Source-Makefile: feeds/packages/utils/crelay/Makefile
Package: crelay
Version: 0.9-1
Depends: +libc +USE_EGLIBC:librt +USE_EGLIBC:libpthread +libftdi1 +hidapi +libusb-1.0
Menu-Depends: 
Provides: 
Build-Depends: !BUILD_NLS:libiconv !BUILD_NLS:libintl
Section: utils
Category: Utilities
Title: USB relay remote control daemon
Maintainer: Ted Hess <thess@kitschensync.net>
Source: crelay-0.9.tar.gz
Type: ipkg
Description:  crelay is used to control different relay cards in a unified manner. It provides
 several interfaces for controlling the relays locally or remotely by a web browser
 or a smartphone.  The card which is detected first will be used. A WebUI control is
 availble on port 8000 (default)
 .
 Currently supported relay cards:
      - Conrad USB 4-channel relay card
      - Sainsmart USB 4-channel relay card
      - Generic GPIO relays
      - HID API compatible relay card
http://github.com/ondrej1024/crelay
Ted Hess <thess@kitschensync.net>
